Distribution . The new species is found in the Lesser Sunda and Sulawesi MEOWs, between 26–66 m depth (
Fig. 2
). The species is known by the common name ‘chicken feet’ and is widespread through the Indo-Pacific as reflected in the collections of Coral Reef Research Foundation, Palau , but not yet described or formally recorded from those localities. The species also occurs in the Bonaparte Gulf MEOW (
Przeslawski et al. 2014
;
Przeslawski et al. 2015
).
